{"title_page": "1974\u201375 Midland Football League", "text_new": "The '''1974\u201375 Midland Football League''' was the 75th in the history of the [[Midland Football League (1889)|Midland Football League]], a [[association football|football]] competition in [[England]].\n\nAt the end of the season the league introduced Division One.\n\n==Premier Division==\n{{Infobox football league season\n|competition= Midland Football League<br>Premier Division\n|season=1974\u201375\n|winners= [[Boston Town F.C.|Boston]]\n|promoted=\n|relegated=\n|matches= 306\n|total goals= 836\n|prevseason= [[1973\u201374 Midland Football League#Premier Division|1973\u201374]]\n|nextseason= [[1975\u201376 Midland Football League#Premier Division|1975\u201376]]\n}}\n\nThe Premier Division featured 15 clubs which competed in the previous season, along with three new clubs:\n*[[Heanor Town F.C.|Heanor Town]], transferred from the [[1973\u201374 West Midlands (Regional) League|West Midlands (Regional) League]]\n*[[Louth United F.C.|Louth United]]\n*[[Mexborough Town Athletic F.C.|Mexborough Town Athletic]], joined from the [[Yorkshire Football League]]\n\n===League table===\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=BOS|name_BOS=[[Boston Town F.C.|Boston]]\n|team2=EAS|name_EAS=[[Eastwood Town F.C.|Eastwood Town]]\n|team3=ALF|name_ALF=[[Alfreton Town F.C.|Alfreton Town]]\n|team4=SKE|name_SKE=[[Skegness Town F.C.|Skegness Town]]\n|team5=ARN|name_ARN=[[Arnold F.C.|Arnold]]\n|team6=MEX|name_MEX=[[Mexborough Town Athletic F.C.|Mexborough Town Athletic]]\n|team7=FRI|name_FRI=[[Frickley Colliery F.C.|Frickley Colliery]]\n|team8=HEA|name_HEA=[[Heanor Town F.C.|Heanor Town]]\n|team9=SUT|name_SUT=[[Ashfield United F.C.|Sutton Town]]\n|team10=ASH|name_ASH=[[Ashby Institute F.C.|Ashby Institute]]\n|team11=RET|name_RET=[[Retford Town F.C.|Retford Town]]\n|team12=BEL|name_BEL=[[Belper Town F.C.|Belper Town]]\n|team13=ILK|name_ILK=[[Ilkeston Town F.C. 