{"title_page": "Association of British Theatre Technicians", "text_new": "{{multipleissues|\n{{third party|date=December 2017}}\n{{barelinks|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name                = Association of British Theatre Technicians\n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| named_after         = \n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| logo                =\n| logo_size           = \n| logo_alt            = \n| logo_caption        = \n| map                 = \n| map_size            = \n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = \n| abbreviation        = \n| motto               = \n| predecessor         = \n| merged              = \n| successor           = \n| formation           = 1961 \n| founder             = \n| founding_location   = \n| extinction          = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| merger              = \n| type                = [[Professional association]]\n| tax_id              = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) -->\n| registration_id     = <!-- for non-profit org -->\n| status              = [[Charitable organisation]]\n| purpose             = To raise [[technical standards]] in the theatre \n| headquarters        = [[London]], {{postcode|EC|1}}<br/>United Kingdom\n| location            = \n| coords              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} -->\n| region              = \n| services            = \n| products            = \n| methods             = \n| fields              = \n| membership          = \n| membership_year     = \n| language            = \n| owner               = <!-- or | owners = -->\n| sec_gen             = \n| leader_title        = \n| leader_name         = \n| leader_title2       = \n| leader_name2        = \n| board_of_directors  = \n| key_people          = \n| main_organ          = \n| parent_organization = \n| subsidiaries        = \n| secessions          = \n| affiliations        = \n| budget              = \n| budget_year         = \n| revenue             = From the ABTT Theatre Show, conferences, training and membership subscriptions\n| revenue_year        = \n| disbursements       = \n| expenses            = \n| expenses_year       = \n| endowment           = \n| staff               = \n| staff_year          = \n| volunteers          = \n| volunteers_year     = \n| slogan              = \n| mission             = \n| website             = [http://www.abtt.org.uk/ www.abtt.org.uk]\n| remarks             = \n| formerly            = \n| footnotes           = \n}}\n'''The Association of British Theatre Technicians''' ('''ABTT''') is a British [[charitable organisation]] representing technical staff working within theatre.\n\n==Overview==\nThe ABTT was founded in 1961 by group of theatre producers, technicians and architects.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2017/mar/02/roderick-ham-obituary</ref> The association has played a role in ensuring that regulations are suitably drafted and enforced, publishing a number of recommended Codes of Practice for the theatrical industry and theatrical technicians.<ref>http://www.abtt.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Code_of_Practice_11.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.etnow.com/news/2012/7/abtt-appoints-fellows-to-acknowledge-outstanding-service-to-theatre-planning</ref>\n\nThe ABTT\u2019s central aim is to \"set out the physical standards for building and their equipment that are necessary to enable to good management of the premises and to provide the safety of the occupants in premises used for entertainment\u201d.<ref>http://www.abtt.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/ABTT-Annual-Report-Audited-Accounts-SIGNED-JC-FINAL.pdf</ref> \nThe ABTT is a [[Charitable Organization]] under English law,<ref>https://apps.charitycommission.gov.uk/Showcharity/RegisterOfCharities/CharityWithPartB.aspx?RegisteredCharityNumber=282069&SubsidiaryNumber=0</ref> and operates throughout [[England]], [[Wales]], [[Northern Ireland]] and [[Scotland]]. The ABTT also has a number of volunteer technical committees which liaise with [[government]] and other organisations.<ref>http://electrical.theiet.org/wiring-matters/60/theatre-installations/index.cfm</ref>\n\n==Membership==\nThe ABTT employs three members of staff. The ABTT is governed by [[Memorandum of association|Memorandum]] and [[Articles of Association]]  and is registered as a [[charitable organisation]] with the [[Charity Commission for England and Wales]]. It has 11 [[trustees]] who are appointed due to their expertise in areas including theatre and [[stage management]], [[architecture]], [[technical theatre]], planning law and the [[performing arts]]. The [[Chairman]] of the Trust is Louise Jeffreys.<ref>http://www.abtt.org.uk/press-release-abtt-announces-new-chairman/</ref>\n\nThe ABTT\u2019s funding is derived from its memberships, donations given by supporters and proceeds from training. The principal source of income is from events including the [[ABTT Theatre Show]] which is held annually.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.artsprofessional.co.uk/magazine/article/21st-century-theatres-abtt-theatre-show-place-management-and-technicians | title=21st Century Theatres \u2013 The ABTT Theatre Show: a place for management and technicians | website=Artsprofessional.co.uk | accessdate=19 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.etnow.com/news/2004/1/abtt-theatre-show-2004|title=ABTT Theatre Show 2004|website=Etnow.com|accessdate=19 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.ropeassemblies.co.uk/july-2016-abtt-theatre-show-2016-see-highly-commended-award-tiger-lifting-chain-block-system/ | title=July 2016 \u2013 ABTT Theatre Show 2016 Highly Commended Award for Tiger Lifting Chain Block System \u2013 Rope Assemblies | date=23 June 2016 | website=Ropeassemblies.co.uk | accessdate=19 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Remit==\nThe ABTT was established by in 1961 with a central focus of ensuring \"the advancement of \u2026the technical subjects connected with theatre and theatrical presentation, fostering knowledge and the appreciation of the art of technical theatre\".<ref>http://www.abtt.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/ABTT-Annual-Report-Audited-Accounts-SIGNED-JC-FINAL.pdf</ref><ref>https://uktheatre.org/who-we-are-what-we-do/uk-theatre-blog/risk-technical-a-new-appointment/</ref>\n\nThe ABTT offers guidance and advice through their Codes of Practice relating to planning, health and safety,<ref>http://www.hse.gov.uk/entertainment/theatre-tv/theatre.htm</ref> architecture regeneration and development, and design which concern theatres and places of entertainment. The ABTT's remit covers a large range of buildings which include both old and new theatres either used, disused or in other uses. Notably, it also includes buildings or structures that have been temporarily converted into theatrical spaces.<ref>http://www.abtt.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Non-Conventional-Theatre-Spaces-17-Aug-2017.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.arts.wales/funding/help-notes/capital-major-additional-notes</ref>\n\n==Resources==\nThe ABTT has a number of resources that contribute towards the promotion of health and safety within theatres and their technical equipment:\n\n* Codes of Practice: The ABTT joined with the [[Health and Safety Executive]] (HSE) to contribute guidance on best practice within a variety of technical theatre fields.<ref>http://www.hse.gov.uk/event-safety/links.htm</ref>\n* Technical Standard for Places of Entertainment \u2013 The ABTT is a contributor for this publication which was produced to offer advice of safe standards and good practice for all types of entertainment premises.{{cn|date=December 2017}}\n* Sightline: The ABTT publishes ''Sightline'' \u2013 Journal for Theatre Technology and Design quarterly.<ref>http://www.etnow.com/sightline/sightline_online/Summer2017/#48</ref> The ABTT also publishes [[health and safety]], [[technical theatre]] books to guide users in [[best practice]].<ref>http://www.etnow.com/sightline/sightline_online/Spring2014/index.html#/36/</ref>\n* Committees \u2013 The Trust maintains a number of committees that collaborate with organisations to further research technical and historical issues.<ref>http://blog.archiveshub.jisc.ac.uk/2016/03/01/the-association-of-performing-arts-collections/</ref><ref>http://blog.archiveshub.jisc.ac.uk/2016/03/01/the-association-of-performing-arts-collections/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.abtt.org.uk/}}\n\n[[Category:1961 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1961]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in the London Borough of Camden]]\n[[Category:Theatrical organisations in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Stage crew]]\n", "text_old": "{{third party|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name                = Association of British Theatre Technicians\n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| named_after         = \n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| logo                =\n| logo_size           = \n| logo_alt            = \n| logo_caption        = \n| map                 = \n| map_size            = \n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = \n| abbreviation        = \n| motto               = \n| predecessor         = \n| merged              = \n| successor           = \n| formation           = 1961 \n| founder             = \n| founding_location   = \n| extinction          = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| merger              = \n| type                = \n| tax_id              = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) -->\n| registration_id     = <!-- for non-profit org -->\n| status              = Charitable Organisation\n| purpose             = To raise [[technical standards]] in the theatre \n| headquarters        = [[London]], {{postcode|EC|1}}<br>United Kingdom\n| location            = \n| coords              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} -->\n| region              = \n| services            = \n| products            = \n| methods             = \n| fields              = \n| membership          = \n| membership_year     = \n| language            = \n| owner               = <!-- or | owners = -->\n| sec_gen             = \n| leader_title        = \n| leader_name         = \n| leader_title2       = \n| leader_name2        = \n| board_of_directors  = \n| key_people          = \n| main_organ          = \n| parent_organization = \n| subsidiaries        = \n| secessions          = \n| affiliations        = \n| budget              = \n| budget_year         = \n| revenue             = From the ABTT Theatre Show, conferences, training and membership subscriptions\n| revenue_year        = \n| disbursements       = \n| expenses            = \n| expenses_year       = \n| endowment           = \n| staff               = \n| staff_year          = \n| volunteers          = \n| volunteers_year     = \n| slogan              = \n| mission             = \n| website             = [www.abtt.org.uk]\n| remarks             = \n| formerly            = \n| footnotes           = \n}}\n'''The Association of British Theatre Technicians''' ('''ABTT''') is a British [[charitable organisation]] representing technical staff working within theatre. It was founded in 1961 by group of theatre producers, technicians and architects. <ref>https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2017/mar/02/roderick-ham-obituary</ref> The ABTT  has played a role in ensuring that regulations are suitably drafted and enforced, publishing a number of recommended Codes of Practice for the theatrical industry and theatrical technicians. <ref>http://www.abtt.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Code_of_Practice_11.pdf</ref><ref> http://www.etnow.com/news/2012/7/abtt-appoints-fellows-to-acknowledge-outstanding-service-to-theatre-planning</ref>\n\nThe ABTT\u2019s central aim is to \"set out the physical standards for building and their equipment that are necessary to enable to good management of the premises and to provide the safety of the occupants in premises used for entertainment\u201d.<ref> http://www.abtt.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/ABTT-Annual-Report-Audited-Accounts-SIGNED-JC-FINAL.pdf</ref> \nThe ABTT is a [[Charitable Organization]] under English law,<ref>https://apps.charitycommission.gov.uk/Showcharity/RegisterOfCharities/CharityWithPartB.aspx?RegisteredCharityNumber=282069&SubsidiaryNumber=0</ref> and operates throughout [[England]], [[Wales]], [[Northern Ireland]] and [[Scotland]]. The ABTT also has a number of volunteer technical committees which liaise with [[government]] and other organisations.<ref>http://electrical.theiet.org/wiring-matters/60/theatre-installations/index.cfm</ref>\n\n==Membership==\nThe ABTT employs three members of staff. The ABTT is governed by [[Memorandum of association|Memorandum]] and [[Articles of Association]]  and is registered as a [[charitable organisation]] with the [[Charity Commission for England and Wales]]. It has 11 [[trustees]] who are appointed due to their expertise in areas including theatre and [[stage management]], [[architecture]], [[technical theatre]], planning law and the [[performing arts]]. The [[Chairman]] of the Trust is Louise Jeffreys.<ref>http://www.abtt.org.uk/press-release-abtt-announces-new-chairman/</ref>\n\nThe ABTT\u2019s funding is derived from its memberships, donations given by supporters and proceeds from training. The principal source of income is from events including the [[ABTT Theatre Show]] which is held annually.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.artsprofessional.co.uk/magazine/article/21st-century-theatres-abtt-theatre-show-place-management-and-technicians|title=21st Century Theatres - The ABTT Theatre Show: a place for management and technicians|website=Artsprofessional.co.uk|accessdate=19 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etnow.com/news/2004/1/abtt-theatre-show-2004|title=ABTT Theatre Show 2004|website=Etnow.com|accessdate=19 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ropeassemblies.co.uk/july-2016-abtt-theatre-show-2016-see-highly-commended-award-tiger-lifting-chain-block-system/|title=July 2016 - ABTT Theatre Show 2016 Highly Commended Award for Tiger Lifting Chain Block System - Rope Assemblies|date=23 June 2016|website=Ropeassemblies.co.uk|accessdate=19 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Remit==\nThe ABTT was established by in 1961 with a central focus of ensuring \"the advancement of \u2026the technical subjects connected with theatre and theatrical presentation, fostering knowledge and the appreciation of the art of technical theatre\". <ref> http://www.abtt.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/ABTT-Annual-Report-Audited-Accounts-SIGNED-JC-FINAL.pdf</ref> <ref>https://uktheatre.org/who-we-are-what-we-do/uk-theatre-blog/risk-technical-a-new-appointment/</ref>\n\nThe ABTT  offers guidance and advice through their Codes of Practice relating to planning, health and safety, <ref>http://www.hse.gov.uk/entertainment/theatre-tv/theatre.htm </ref>\narchitecture regeneration and development, and design which concern theatres and places of entertainment.  The ABTT's remit covers a large range of buildings which include both old and new theatres either used, disused or in other uses. Notably, it also includes buildings or structures that have been temporarily converted into theatrical spaces.<ref> http://www.abtt.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Non-Conventional-Theatre-Spaces-17-Aug-2017.pdf</ref> <ref>http://www.arts.wales/funding/help-notes/capital-major-additional-notes</ref>  \n\n==Resources==\nThe ABTT has a number of resources that contribute towards the promotion of health and safety within theatres and their technical equipment:\n*Codes of Practice: The ABTT joined with the [[Health and Safety Executive]] (HSE) to contribute guidance on best practice within a variety of technical theatre fields.<ref>http://www.hse.gov.uk/event-safety/links.htm</ref>\n\n* Technical Standard for Places of Entertainment \u2013 The ABTT is a contributor for this publication which was produced to offer advice of safe standards and good practice for all types of entertainment premises.{{cn|date=December 2017}}\n\n*Sightline: The ABTT publishes ''Sightline'' - Journal for Theatre Technology and Design quarterly.<ref>http://www.etnow.com/sightline/sightline_online/Summer2017/#48</ref> The ABTT also publishes [[health and safety]], [[technical theatre]] books to guide users in [[best practice]].<ref>http://www.etnow.com/sightline/sightline_online/Spring2014/index.html#/36/</ref>\n\n*Committees - The Trust maintains a number of committees that collaborate with organisations to further research technical and historical issues. <ref>http://blog.archiveshub.jisc.ac.uk/2016/03/01/the-association-of-performing-arts-collections/</ref> <ref>http://blog.archiveshub.jisc.ac.uk/2016/03/01/the-association-of-performing-arts-collections/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|www.abtt.org.uk}}\n\n[[Category:Stage crew]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in the London Borough of Camden]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1961]]\n[[Category:Theatrical organisations in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:1961 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "Jpbowen", "label": "safe", "comment": "Tidying, refs, bare links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Association_of_British_Theatre_Technicians"}
