{"title_page": "A Change of Heart (The 1975 song)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = A Change of Heart\n| cover      = The 1975 - A Change of Heart.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[The 1975]]\n| album      = [[I Like It When You Sleep, for You Are So Beautiful Yet So Unaware of It]]\n| released   = 22 February 2016 {{small|(Radio)}}<br>15 March 2016 {{small|(Single)}}\n| format     =\n| recorded   = 2015\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Art pop]]<ref name=\"napster\">{{cite web |title=The 1975\u2019s Sprawling, Ambitious \u2018I Like It When You Sleep\u2019 |url=https://blog.napster.com/2016/02/29/the-1975s-sprawling-ambitious-i-like-it-when-you-sleep/ |website=Napster |accessdate=30 August 2019}}</ref>|[[synth-pop]]<ref name=\"napster\"/>|[[sophisti-pop]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Binns |first1=Maddie |title=Dream Setlist: The 1975 |url=https://www.festicket.com/magazine/features/dream-setlist-1975/ |website=Festicket |accessdate=14 September 2019 |date=28 May 2019}}</ref>}}\n| length     = 4:43\n| label      = [[Dirty Hit]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|George Daniel|Adam Hann|Matthew Healy|Ross MacDonald}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Mike Crossey]]|George Daniel|Matthew Healy}}\n| prev_title = [[The Sound (The 1975 song)|The Sound]]\n| prev_year  = 2016\n| next_title = [[She's American]]\n| next_year  = 2016\n| misc       = \n{{External music video|{{YouTube|trbwqF0d7NA|\"A Change of Heart\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''A Change of Heart'''\" is a song by English [[Rock music|rock]] band [[The 1975]]. It was released as a radio and streaming single on 22 February 2016<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web |last1=Britton |first1=Luke Morgan |title=Listen to The 1975\u2019s new album track \u2018A Change Of Heart\u2019 |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-34-1197043 |website=NME |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=23 February 2016}}</ref> with a physical single released on 15 March 2016<ref>{{discogs release|8256800|A Change of Heart - Single}}</ref>, and the corresponding music video coming on 21 April 2016.\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for the single was released on 21 April 2016 on the band's [[YouTube]] channel. The music video features lead singer Matty Healey dressed up as a [[clown]] at an empty carnival dancing with a female clown while also playing carnival games and riding in bumper cars, before ultimately, the female clown leaves Healy.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Helman |first1=Peter |title=The 1975 \u2013 \u201cA Change Of Heart\u201d Video |url=https://www.stereogum.com/1872975/the-1975-a-change-of-heart-video/video/ |website=Stereogum |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=21 April 2016}}</ref> The music video is an allude to commedia dell\u2019arte, or classical Italian comedy given the mime-like clown characteristics, which resemble a Pierrot character.<ref name=\"spin review music vid\">{{cite web |last1=Gaca |first1=Anna |title=The 1975\u2019s \u2018A Change of Heart\u2019 Video Will Break Yours |url=https://www.spin.com/2016/04/the-1975-a-change-of-heart-video-watch/ |website=Spin |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=22 April 2016}}</ref> In ''Coup de Main'' magazine, it was revealed the various sources that were used to inspire the music video to \"A Change of Heart\". The mood of the music video was to allude to [[Federico Fellini]]'s 1970 movie, ''[[I clowns]]''.<ref name=\"graves\">{{cite web |last1=Graves |first1=Shahlin |title=Matty Healy explains The 1975's 'A Change of Heart' music video |url=https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/tidbits/matty-healy-explains-1975s-change-heart-music-video |website=coupdemainmagazine.com |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=26 April 2016}}</ref> Choreographing was inspired by various dances by [[Michael Jackson]], [[Gene Kelly]], and [[Bob Fosse]]. The monochrome coloring was used to be used \"for the sake of subtext and self reference\".<ref name=\"graves\"/> The film was released entirely in black-and-white, and was directed by Tim Mattia and choreographed by Katie Collins.<ref>{{cite web |title=The 1975 break our hearts in their new music video, \u201cA Change of Heart\u201d |url=http://outletmag.co/the-1975-break-our-hearts-in-their-new-music-video-a-change-of-heart/ |website=Outlet |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=24 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nAnna Gaca of [[Spin (magazine)|''Spin'']] magazine praised the music video saying that \"A Change of Heart music video will break your [heart]\".<ref name=\"spin review music vid\"/> Madelin Roth, writing for [[MTV]] called the music video \"bittersweet sweet-turned-sour relationship\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roth |first1=Madelin |title=See A Tragic Clown Romance Unfold in The 1975 'A Change of Heart' Music Video |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2872229/the-1975-a-change-of-heart-video/ |website=MTV |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=22 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Live performances ==\nThe song made its television debut on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' in November 2016.<ref>{{cite AV media |date=25 November 2016 |title=The 1975 - A Change Of Heart (Live from \"Late Night with Seth Meyers\") |medium=Video |language=English |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nwU2a4Jktto |access-date=29 August 2019 |time= |location=[[New York City]] |publisher=[[NBCUniversal Television Distribution]]}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2016)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|127|date=13 March 2016|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 August 2019}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardrocksongs|47|artist=The 1975|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 August 2019}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardalternativesongs|36|artist=The 1975|rowheader=true|accessdate=13 May 2019}}\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Discogs release|8256800|A Change of Heart - Single}}\n\n{{The 1975}}\n\n[[Category:2016 singles]]\n[[Category:2016 songs]]\n[[Category:Black-and-white music videos]]\n[[Category:Dirty Hit singles]]\n[[Category:Polydor Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Matthew Healy]]\n[[Category:The 1975 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = A Change of Heart\n| cover      = The 1975 - A Change of Heart.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[The 1975]]\n| album      = [[I Like It When You Sleep, for You Are So Beautiful Yet So Unaware of It]]\n| released   = 22 February 2016 {{small|(Radio)}}<br>15 March 2016 {{small|(Single)}}\n| format     =\n| recorded   = 2015\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Art pop]]<ref name=\"napster\">{{cite web |title=The 1975\u2019s Sprawling, Ambitious \u2018I Like It When You Sleep\u2019 |url=https://blog.napster.com/2016/02/29/the-1975s-sprawling-ambitious-i-like-it-when-you-sleep/ |website=Napster |accessdate=30 August 2019}}</ref>|[[synth-pop]]<ref name=\"napster\"/>|[[sophisti-pop]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Binns |first1=Maddie |title=Dream Setlist: The 1975 |url=https://www.festicket.com/magazine/features/dream-setlist-1975/ |website=Festicket |accessdate=14 September 2019 |date=28 May 2019}}</ref>}}\n| length     = 4:43\n| label      = [[Dirty Hit]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|George Daniel|Adam Hann|Matthew Healy|Ross MacDonald}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Mike Crossey]]|George Daniel|Matthew Healy}}\n| prev_title = [[The Sound (The 1975 song)|The Sound]]\n| prev_year  = 2016\n| next_title = [[She's American]]\n| next_year  = 2016\n| misc       = \n{{External music video|{{YouTube|trbwqF0d7NA|\"A Change of Heart\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''A Change of Heart'''\" is a song by English [[Rock music|rock]] band [[The 1975]]. It was released as a radio and streaming single on 22 February 2016<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite web |last1=Britton |first1=Luke Morgan |title=Listen to The 1975\u2019s new album track \u2018A Change Of Heart\u2019 |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-34-1197043 |website=NME |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=23 February 2016}}</ref> with a physical single released on 15 March 2016<ref>{{discogs release|8256800|A Change of Heart - Single}}</ref>, and the corresponding music video coming on 21 April 2016.\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for the single was released on 21 April 2016 on the band's [[YouTube]] channel. The music video features lead singer Matty Healey dressed up as a [[clown]] at an empty carnival dancing with a female clown while also playing carnival games and riding in bumper cars, before ultimately, the female clown leaves Healy.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Helman |first1=Peter |title=The 1975 \u2013 \u201cA Change Of Heart\u201d Video |url=https://www.stereogum.com/1872975/the-1975-a-change-of-heart-video/video/ |website=Stereogum |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=21 April 2016}}</ref> The music video is an allude to commedia dell\u2019arte, or classical Italian comedy given the mime-like clown characteristics, which resemble a Pierrot character.<ref name=\"spin review music vid\">{{cite web |last1=Gaca |first1=Anna |title=The 1975\u2019s \u2018A Change of Heart\u2019 Video Will Break Yours |url=https://www.spin.com/2016/04/the-1975-a-change-of-heart-video-watch/ |website=Spin |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=22 April 2016}}</ref> In ''Coup de Main'' magazine, it was revealed the various sources that were used to inspire the music video to \"A Change of Heart\". The mood of the music video was to allude to [[Federico Fellini]]'s 1970 movie, ''[[I clowns]]''.<ref name=\"graves\">{{cite web |last1=Graves |first1=Shahlin |title=Matty Healy explains The 1975's 'A Change of Heart' music video |url=https://www.coupdemainmagazine.com/tidbits/matty-healy-explains-1975s-change-heart-music-video |website=coupdemainmagazine.com |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=26 April 2016}}</ref> Choreographing was inspired by various dances by [[Michael Jackson]], [[Gene Kelly]], and [[Bob Fosse]]. The monochrome coloring was used to be used \"for the sake of subtext and self reference\".<ref name=\"graves\"/> The film was released entirely in black-and-white, and was directed by Tim Mattia and choreographed by Katie Collins.<ref>{{cite web |title=The 1975 break our hearts in their new music video, \u201cA Change of Heart\u201d |url=http://outletmag.co/the-1975-break-our-hearts-in-their-new-music-video-a-change-of-heart/ |website=Outlet |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=24 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nAnna Gaca of [[Spin (magazine)|''Spin'']] magazine praised the music video saying that \"A Change of Heart music video will break your [heart]\".<ref name=\"spin review music vid\"/> Madelin Roth, writing for [[MTV]] called the music video \"bittersweet sweet-turned-sour relationship\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roth |first1=Madelin |title=See A Tragic Clown Romance Unfold in The 1975 'A Change of Heart' Music Video |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2872229/the-1975-a-change-of-heart-video/ |website=MTV |accessdate=30 August 2019 |date=22 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Live performances ==\nThe song made its television debut on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' in November 2016.<ref>{{cite AV media |date=25 November 2016 |title=The 1975 - A Change Of Heart (Live from \"Late Night with Seth Meyers\") |medium=Video |language=English |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nwU2a4Jktto |access-date=29 August 2019 |time= |location=[[New York City]] |publisher=[[NBCUniversal Television Distribution]]}}</ref>\n\n== Charting ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2016)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|127|date=13 March 2016|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 August 2019}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardrocksongs|47|artist=The 1975|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 August 2019}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardalternativesongs|36|artist=The 1975|rowheader=true|accessdate=13 May 2019}}\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Discogs 