or)\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Dmitri Bulykin]] (Dynamo Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Georgia}} [[Mikheil Ashvetia]] (Lokomotiv Moscow)\n{{col-2}}\n;Left forwards\n#{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Aleksandr Kerzhakov]] (Zenit)\n#{{flagicon|Croatia}} [[Ivica Oli\u0107]] (CSKA Moscow)\n#{{flagicon|Brazil}} [[Roni\u00e9liton dos Santos|Roni]] (Rubin)\n{{Col-end}}\n</center>\n\n==Medal squads==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" Width=\"700\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#FF0000\"\n| align=\"center\" width=\"700\" |<span style=\"color:#0000FF;\"> '''1. PFC CSKA Moscow''' </span>\n|- bgcolor=\"#E8E8E8\"  \n| align=\"left\" width=\"700\" |\n'''Goalkeepers:''' [[Veniamin Mandrykin]] (19), [[Igor Akinfeev]] (13).<br />\n'''Defenders:''' [[Aleksei Berezutski]] (30), [[Bohdan Shershun]] {{flagicon|UKR}} (27 / 1), [[Denis Yevsikov]] (24), [[Vasili Berezutski]] (23), [[Deividas \u0160emberas]] {{flagicon|LTU}} (21), [[Andrei Solomatin]] (20).<br />\n'''Midfielders:''' [[Elvir Rahimi\u0107]] {{flagicon|BIH}} (28 / 1), [[Ji\u0159\u00ed Jaro\u0161\u00edk]] {{flagicon|CZE}} (27 / 7), [[Rolan Gusev]] (26 / 9), [[Igor Yanovsky]] (25 / 5), [[Sergei Semak]] (24 / 7), [[Juris Laiz\u0101ns]] {{flagicon|LVA}} (21 / 1), [[Spartak Gogniyev]] (11 / 2), [[Alan Kusov]] (11), [[Artur Tlisov]] (3 / 1).<br />\n'''Forwards:''' [[Denis Popov]] (22 / 8), [[Dmitri Kirichenko]] (22 / 5), [[Ivica Oli\u0107]] {{flagicon|CRO}} (10 / 7), [[Alexander Geynrikh]] {{flagicon|UZB}} (2 / 1), [[Sergey Samodin]] (2), [[Vardan Mazalov]] (1).<br />''(league appearances and goals listed in brackets)''\n\nOne own goal scored by [[Andr\u00e9s Scotti]] {{flagicon|URU}} ([[FC Rubin Kazan]]).\n\n'''Manager:''' [[Valery Gazzaev]].\n\n'''Transferred out during the season:''' [[Alan Kusov]] (on loan to [[FC Spartak-Alania Vladikavkaz]]).\n|- bgcolor=\"#0000FF\"\n| align=\"center\" width=\"700\" |<span style=\"color:#FFFFFF;\"> '''2. FC Zenit St. Petersburg''' </span>\n|- bgcolor=\"#E8E8E8\"\n| align=\"left\" width=\"700\" |\n'''Goalkeepers:''' [[Vyacheslav Malafeev]] (